Description

The AppointmentController class handles the CRUD operations for Appointments and manages the display and behavior of the appointments UI.
Appointments
Represents an appointment with various attributes and details.
AppointmentUpdateController
Controller for updating appointments.
ContactAccess
This class represents the data access object (DAO) responsible for retrieving and handling contact-related data from a database using JDBC.
Contacts
The Contacts class represents a contact entity with attributes such as ID, name, and email.
Country
Represents a country with a unique identifier and its name.
CountryAccess
The CountryAccess class provides methods to access and manage country information in the database.

The CustomerAccess class provides methods to access and manage customer information in the database.

This class serves as a controller for the Add Customer screen.
CustomerController
Controller for managing customer records.
Customers
The Customers class represents customer information including their ID, name, address, postal code, phone number, division ID, and division name.
CustomerUpdateController
The CustomerUpdateController class provides methods and event handlers to manage the updating of customer records.
FirstLevelDivision
The FirstLevelDivision class represents a geographical or administrative division within a country.
FirstLevelDivisionAccess
The FirstLevelDivisionAccess class provides methods to access and manage first-level division information in the database.
General
Utility class containing methods and nested classes for general purposes such as scene transitions, alerts, validations, and more.

Singleton class responsible for managing the primary stage.
JDBC
JDBC Helper class provides utility methods to manage database connectivity.
LoginController
The LoginController class provides methods to handle user login actions, log login attempts, and adjust the locale based on the system's settings.
Main
The Main class creates an application for inventory management and adds sample data.
MainScreenController
This class provides the controller for the main screen of the application.
ReportAccess
The ReportAccess class provides methods to access and generate reports related to appointments and countries.
ReportController
The ReportController class manages and controls the report view for the application.
ReportMonth
The ReportMonth class encapsulates information about the total number of appointments for a specific month.
Reports
The Reports class holds information about custom reports, including country counts and names.
ReportType
The ReportType class encapsulates information about the total number of appointments for a specific appointment type.
TimeUtility
TimeUtility class provides utility methods for managing and converting time.
UserAccess
The UserAccess class provides methods to access and manipulate user-related data from the database.
Users
The Users class represents user information, including their ID, name, and password.
